 are the building blocks of policy change and better practices. With on the ground dos and don'ts easily pursued in our daily lives, In This Together shows us a practical and hopeful way forward into our shared future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aClimate change mitigationxCitizen participation. 0aClimatic changesxEffect of human beings on. 0aEnvironmental policyxCitizen participation. 0aEnvironmental protectionxCitizen participation. 4aEDUCATION & HISTORY OF EDUCATION. 4aENVIRONMENT. 4aGeneral Science. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  afood waste and climate change, environmental education, climate change and global connections, climate change and volunteering, network climate action, climate change and individual behaviors, behavioral change and social influence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176858340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501768583423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501768583/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK